    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/wcl/fbh/6042178087.html"></div>
        </div>
Hotel Arista is not a chain, rather, we're something a little different. We're an independent, locally owned boutique hotel and something of a maverick. We offer effortless and luxurious accommodations for business, leisure and weddings.<br>
<br>
Our guests are people who like to write their own story -- leaders, innovators, high-profile couples, chic brides, authors, actors, film crews and more. This is a crowd that likes the seduction of an effortless, evocative experience and the glamour of making a place their own. Personal taste and choice are considered paramount at Hotel Arista, and guests select from an extensive personal preference menu of amenities and services.<br>
<br>
Role Summary:<br>
This individual is responsible for assisting the Outlets Manager in the overall management of the daily operations of the restaurant. The Restaurant Manger will be visibly present on the floor during service and will be available to take feedback from guests. This position will take complete responsibility for the restaurant operations in the absence of the Outlets Manager.<br>
<br>
Responsibilities:<br>
-Organizes and conduct pre-shift and departmental meetings.<br>
-Assists with the creation and development of community outreach and marketing plans to penetrate new sales opportunities and maximize use within existing markets<br>
-Conducts ongoing training programs for new and existing employees<br>
-Ability to multi-task and prioritize in a deadline driven, demanding environment.<br>
-Coordinates with the F&B, Sales, and Convention Services team for group events<br>
-Organizes special events in the restaurant.<br>
-Checks for food quality and service consistency.<br>
-Assists with the inventories for the F&B liquor control.<br>
-Provides a positive, empowering, and productive work environment through setting an example and consistency of daily work habits and standards.<br>
-Instructs new hires and employees on the expectations and responsibilities for each of their roles.<br>
-Interacts positively with customers promoting hotel facilities and services.<br>
-Analyzes, investigates, and resolves guest complaints.<br>
<br>
Requirements:<br>
<br>
Education<br>
-College graduate or equivalent work experience<br>
-BASSET or TIPS certification preferred<br>
<br>
Experience<br>
-Two or more years experience as a manager in a full server, fine dining restaurant.<br>
-Micros experience preferred<br>
-Knowledge of fine dining, wines, and great service leadership.<br>
<br>
Skills<br>
-Excellent verbal and written skills<br>
-Neat an clean appearance<br>
-Ability to work in a team environment<br>
-Must have problem solving abilities, and the ability to compute basic arithmetic.<br>
-Must have a flexible schedule and be available to work nights weekends, and holidays.<br>
<br>
Physical Requirements<br>
-Must be able to walk and stand for up to 8 hours a day, with or without reasonable accommodation<br>
-Must be able to bend, stoop, squat, and stretch to fulfill job duties.<br>
-Must be able to lift up to 25 lbs regularly.<br>
 <br>
We are an equal opportunity employer and make employment decisions without regard to age, race, religion, national origin, gender, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation and gender identity or any other protected class. Our locations are drug-free and pre-employment drug tests are required. Background checks are also required before employment begins. <br>
<br>
We participate in E-Verify and those who are ineligible to work in the United States will not be considered.    </section>

